---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Illustration from '../components/Illustration.astro';
---

<Layout title="Welcome to Astro.">
	<section class="h-[64px] relative z-10 text-sm">
		<div class="container px-4 flex flex-row justify-between items-center h-full">
			<div>
				<span>Luka Ivanović © 2024</span>
			</div>

			<div class="flex flex-row justify-between w-[560px]">
				<span>LinkedIn</span>
				<span>Twitter</span>
				<span>hi@ivanovicluka.co</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="h-[calc(100vh-64px)] pb-[64px] overflow-hidden">
		<div class="container px-4 h-full flex flex-row ">
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-end h-full w-1/2 z-10">
				<h1>Software designer at weweb<br />working on allowing anyone<br /> to build web applications </h1>
			</div>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-end h-full w-1/2 relative">
				<Illustration />
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class=" pt-[240px]">
		<div class="container px-4 flex flex-row items-center">
			<div class="h-[1px] w-[8px] bg-neutral-200"></div>
			<div class=" w-[32px] h-[32px] bg-black border border-4 border-white outline outline-1 outline-black z-10">
				
			</div>
			
			<div class="h-[1px] flex-grow bg-neutral-200"></div>
		</div>
		<div class="container px-4 flex flex-row justify-between pt-[64px]">
			<div class="w-1/2">
				<h2>WeWeb Editor</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="w-[560px]">
				<p>The editor features many complex and intertwining systems such as components, workflows and more. We take web best practices and present them in an elevated and clear interface. As a result, editor can export clean and modern code.

					Visit website</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class=" pt-[240px]">
		<div class="container px-4 flex flex-row items-center">
			<div class="h-[1px] w-[8px] bg-neutral-200"></div>
			<svg class="w-[32px] h-[32px] bg-black"></svg>
			<div class="h-[1px] flex-grow bg-neutral-200"></div>
		</div>
		<div class="container px-4 flex flex-row justify-between pt-[64px] pb-[120px]">
			<div class="w-1/2">
				<h2>WeWeb Components</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="w-[560px]">
				<p>Offering basic UI components is essential for any app builder to compete with the vast number of libraries available in standard coding approaches. However, a common limitation among most app builders is the lack of deep customizability.
<br/>
<br/>

					Inspired by the power of Radix and the aesthetics of Shadcn libraries in the coding world, we set out to revamp our element toolkit, focusing on full customizability, functionality and accessibility.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="container grid grid-cols-2 gap-[16px] h-[620px]">
			<div class=" bg-black">
			</div>
			<div class=" bg-black">
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section>
		<div class="container h-[500px] flex flex-col justify-end items-center py-4">
			<span>Luka Ivanović © 2024</span>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
	@font-face {
		font-family: 'TWK Lausanne';
		src: url('/fonts/TWKLausanne.woff2') format('woff2');
		font-weight: normal;
		font-style: normal;
		font-display: swap;
	}

	body {
		font-family: 'TWK Lausanne', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 350;
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1464px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 50px;
		line-height: 58px;
		font-weight: 350;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 50px;
		line-height: 58px;
		font-weight: 350;
	}

	p {
		font-size: 17px;
		line-height: 30px;
	}
</style>
